						<summary>

						<p>Four sides of a pillar lying in the Inspection Bungalow.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The fourth face of the pillar (No. 27) seems to contain an independent inscription. It is very much damaged, hence much of the information is lost. It begins with imprecatory verses and seems to have recorded some grants, the details of which are lost.</p>						

						<p>It contains no date but palaeographically assignable to the period of the previous record [No. 27] 1056 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
